---
layout: layouts/base
---

{% from "macros.njk" import logo, icon %}

<style>
  /*
    Resize all .containers, including the footer.container
    which is in the inherited base layout.
  */
  .container {
    max-width: calc(640px + 2rem);
  }
</style>

<div class="h-1 bg-indigo-600 dark:bg-indigo-400"></div>
<div class="home container shrink-0 grow">
  <header class="py-24 border-b">
    <a
      class="
        inline-flex items-center mb-5 -ml-1
        no-underline text-xl font-mono tracking-tight
      "
      href="{{ '/' | url }}"
    >
      {{ logo(class='mr-1.5', width=28, height=28) }}
      thinkdev
    </a>
    <h1>{{ site.title }}</h1>
    <p class="mb-14">
      <b class="lead">Let's relearn the basics of programming together,
      in the world's most popular language &mdash; JavaScript<a href="#0" class="no-underline"
      ><cite class="not-italic align-sup">*</cite></a>.</b>
    </p>
    <a href="#lessons" class="inline-flex items-center no-underline">
      Skip to lessons
      {{ icon('arrow-down', class='ml-1.5') }}
    </a>
  </header>

  <main>
    <section class="py-24 border-b">
      <h2>Go beyond the usuals.</h2>
      <p>
        We'll learn the usual things in programming &mdash; variables, functions, loops,
        and what have you &mdash; but we won't stop there.
      </p>
      <p>
        As developers, we also have to test our code,
        track down and fix errors, and write documentation to explain our code to others
        (and ourselves).
      </p>
      <p>
        We'll learn how to do these too, and we'll use some tools that make
        the process fun ðŸ˜ƒ.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="py-24 border-b">
      <h2>What to expect?</h2>
      <p>At the end of the course, you should be able to</p>
      <ul class="list-['âœ”']">
        <li>analyze problems and come up with solutions</li>
        <li>express solutions in JavaScript</li>
        <li>document, test, and debug simple programs</li>
        <li>use some common data structures and algorithms</li>
        <li>use the command line</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="py-24 border-b">
      <h2 id="lessons">Lessons</h2>
    </section>

    <section class="py-24 border-b">
      <h2>Format</h2>
      <div class="note note-info">
        <p>
          <strong>Tip:</strong>
          Press the question mark key (<kbd>?</kbd>) when viewing
          the interactive slides to see a list of keyboard shortcuts.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="py-24 border-b">
      <h2>It's not just JavaScript</h2>
    </section>

    <div class="py-24 border-b">
      <p
        class="flex items-center -ml-1 text-xl font-mono tracking-tight"
        href="{{ '/' | url }}"
      >
        {{ logo(class='mr-1.5', width=28, height=28) }}
        thinkdev
      </p>
    </div>

    <footer class="py-24">
      <h2>References</h2>
    </footer>
  </main>

  <main id="main" class="prose prose-indigo py-10 dark:prose-invert">
    <section>
      <h2>What we'll do</h2>
      <ul class="list-['âœ”']">
        <li>Learn how to break down problems</li>
        <li>Express solutions in a programming language (JavaScript)</li>
        <li>Get familiar with the command line</li>
        <li>Practise documenting, testing, and debugging</li>
        <li>Use some common data structures and algorithms</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Lessons</h2>
      <ol>
        {% for lesson in collections.all | eleventyNavigation %}
          <li><a href="{{ lesson.url | url }}">{{ lesson.title }}</a></li>
        {%- endfor %}
      </ol>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Format</h2>
      <!--
        We'll meet on Saturdays for a discussion and review of the previous week's lesson.
        On Sundays, we'll meet for a new lesson.
        Meetings will hold on Zoom from 12:00 p.m. to 12:40 p.m.
      -->
      <p>
        Each lesson page contains the slides, recorded meetings,
        exercises, etc., for that lesson. The slides are in two formats:
        an interactive presentation that you can view on this site
        and a PDF version that you can download.
      </p>

      <div class="note note-info">
        <p>
          <strong>Tip:</strong>
          Press the question mark key (<kbd>?</kbd>) when viewing
          the interactive slides to see a list of keyboard shortcuts.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Credits</h2>
      {% set bindingsLesson = collections.all | eleventyNavigation | find('title', 'Bindings again') %}
      <ul>
        <li>
          <a href="https://greenteapress.com/wp/think-python-2e/"><cite>Think Python</cite> by Allen Downey</a>.
          The book is also known by the title <i>How to Think Like a Computer Scientist</i>.
          Yes, it inspired this course's title ðŸ™‚.
        </li>
        <li>
          The <a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript"><cite>MDN Web Docs</cite></a>.
          My primary reference for this course.
          It's a great place to learn JavaScript and other things web-related.
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="https://eloquentjavascript.net/"><cite class="quoted">Eloquent JavaScript</cite></a>.
          An introductory yet thorough book on programming in modern JavaScript.
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="https://tc39.es/ecma262/"><cite>The ECMAScript Language Specification</cite></a> (ECMA 262).
          The document that formally defines what the JavaScript language is.
        </li>
        <li>
          The prerelease draft of the
          <a href="https://justjavascript.com/"><cite>Just JavaScript</cite> course</a>.
          The course focuses on building a good mental model of JavaScript.
          It inspired the fifth episode of this thinkdev course,
          <a href="{{ bindingsLesson.url | url }}">{{ bindingsLesson.title or "Bindings again" }}</a>.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <p>And just for fun ðŸ˜ƒ ...</p>
      <p>
        I built this site with <a href="https://www.11ty.dev/">Eleventy</a>,
        <a href="https://tailwindcss.com/">Tailwind CSS</a>, and
        <a href="https://revealjs.com/">reveal.js</a> (for the slides),
        and hosted it on <a href="http://netlify.com/">Netlify</a>.
      </p>
    </section>


  </main>

</div>


